""" Ensure possible groups are only adjacent numbers after identifing some groups containing nans"""
self.col.group(4.0, self.col._nan)
self.col.group(3.0, 4.0)
self.col.group(3.0, 2.0)
groupings = [(self.col.metadata[x], self.col.metadata[y]) for x, y in self.
    col.possible_groupings()]
possible_groupings = [(1.0, 3.0), (3.0, 5.0)]
assert list_unordered_equal(possible_groupings, groupings
    ), 'With NaNs, with groups containing nan identified, possible grouping incorrectly identified.'
groups = [[self.col.metadata[i] for i in group] for group in self.col.groups()]
actual_groups = [[1.0], [2.0, 3.0, 4.0, '<missing>'], [5.0], [10.0]]
assert list_unordered_equal(actual_groups, groups
    ), 'With NaNs, with groups containing nan identified, actual groupings are incorrectly reported'
